abstract:
Poly (linolenic acid)-g-poly (caprolactone)-g-poly (t-butyl acrylate) (PLilPCLPtBA) graft copolymer was used as an interfacial layer in Au/n-Si Schottky diode. The novel PLilPCLPtBA layer was coated on n-Si single crystal wafer through an electrospinning system. Nanofiber characteristics of the PLilPCLPtBA layer was obtained by a Field Emission Scanning Electron Microscope (FEG-SEM). The current–voltage (I–V) measurements of these Au/n-Si diodes with and without polymeric layer were conducted in dark and under various illumination intensity levels (halogen lamp) at room temperature. Main electrical parameters such as series resistance (R

                        s
                     ), shunt resistance (R

                        sh
                     ), ideality factor (n), reverse saturation current (I

                        o
                     ), zero-bias barrier height (Φ

                        bo
                     ) and interface state density (N

                        ss
                     ) of the structures were extracted from forward-bias I–V data.

